# Cursor Rules for cesargdm.com

## Project Overview
This is cesargdm.com - a high-performance personal website built with modern web technologies. The site features:
- 🌍 **Internationalization support**
- 🖼️ **Dynamic OG Image Generation**  
- 📄 **Markdown-driven content**
- 🔍 **Algolia Search Integration**
- 🏆 **Perfect Lighthouse Score** (Performance, Accessibility, SEO)
- 🤖 **Custom OpenAI Agent**
- 💅 **Zero Runtime CSS** with Vanilla Extract

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15.3.4 (App Router)
- **React**: 19.1.0 
- **TypeScript**: 5.8.3
- **Styling**: Vanilla Extract CSS (@vanilla-extract/css)
- **Package Manager**: Bun (preferred)
- **Deployment**: Vercel
- **Search**: Algolia
- **AI**: OpenAI integration

## Quality & Build Verification (MANDATORY)

### Always Run These Checks Before Any Code Changes
```bash
# 1. TypeScript type checking
bun run typecheck

# 2. ESLint with zero warnings policy
bun run lint

# 3. Prettier format checking
bun run format:check

# 4. Build verification
bun run build
```

### Before Committing Changes
```bash
# Format code
bun run format

# Verify all checks pass
bun run typecheck && bun run lint && bun run build
```

## Modern Next.js 15 & React 19 Best Practices

### App Router Patterns
- Use the `app/` directory structure (already implemented)
- Prefer Server Components by default, use Client Components only when needed
- Use `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, and `not-found.tsx` for UI states
- Implement proper metadata API for SEO

### React 19 Best Practices
- Use the new `use()` hook for async operations in components
- Leverage React Server Actions for form handling
- Use React.lazy() with Suspense for code splitting
- Prefer function declarations for named components (enforced by ESLint)

### Performance Optimization
- Always implement proper image optimization with `next/image`
- Use dynamic imports for large dependencies
- Implement proper caching strategies
- Maintain the perfect Lighthouse score standard

### TypeScript Best Practices
- Use strict TypeScript configuration (already configured)
- Implement proper type imports (`import type`) as enforced by ESLint
- Use the `satisfies` operator for type assertion when appropriate
- Define proper interfaces for API responses and data structures

## Styling Guidelines (Vanilla Extract CSS)

### CSS-in-TypeScript Patterns
- Create `.css.ts` files for component styles
- Use design tokens and consistent spacing/color systems
- Implement responsive designs with breakpoint utilities
- Avoid runtime CSS dependencies (zero runtime requirement)

### File Organization
```
src/
├── components/     # Reusable UI components
├── modules/        # Feature-specific modules  
├── app/           # Next.js App Router pages
├── lib/           # Utilities and configurations
└── assets/        # Static assets
```

## Code Quality Rules

### ESLint Configuration
- **Zero warnings policy**: `--max-warnings=0` is enforced
- Accessibility rules are strict (jsx-a11y/strict)
- Import sorting is automated with specific group ordering
- React-specific rules for performance and best practices

### Import Organization (Automated)
1. Node.js and React packages
2. Internal screens/navigation/containers  
3. Modules
4. Components
5. Library/utility functions
6. Internal modules
7. Side effect imports
8. Parent directory imports
9. Relative imports
10. Style imports (CSS files last)

### Performance Rules
- Avoid magic numbers (exceptions: -1, 0, 1, 2)
- No console.log in production code
- Proper React key usage
- Prevent leaked renders and unnecessary fragments

## Development Workflow

### Starting Development
```bash
# Preferred package manager
bun dev

# Verify localhost:3000 loads correctly
```

### After Each Agent Session (MANDATORY)
```bash
# ALWAYS run after agent completes any changes
bun run format

# Optional: Run full quality verification
bun run typecheck && bun run lint && bun run build
```

### Before Pushing Changes
1. Run full quality checks: `bun run typecheck && bun run lint && bun run build`
2. Verify Lighthouse score remains perfect (if UI changes)
3. Test internationalization features (if applicable)
4. Verify search functionality (if content changes)

## Internationalization Guidelines
- Use proper i18n patterns for multi-language support
- Implement locale-aware routing
- Ensure proper metadata for each language variant

## API & Data Handling
- Use TypeScript for all API interfaces
- Implement proper error handling
- Use React Server Actions for mutations when possible
- Maintain OpenAI integration patterns for the custom agent

## Security & Performance
- Implement proper Content Security Policy
- Use Next.js Image optimization for all images
- Maintain zero runtime CSS requirement
- Follow Vercel deployment best practices

## Emergency Override
If any of these rules prevent urgent fixes, document the reason and create a follow-up task to address the rule compliance.